This paper discusses the field of Explainable AI (XAI) and its application in improving human task performance in the game of Chess. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with the development of intelligent agents and their applications. The paper also involves a user study, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of machine learning models and their performance evaluation falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the game theory aspect of Chess can be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves the generation of rationales, which can be considered as a form of explanation, and thus falls under cs.CY (Computational Complexity and Cryptography).
